# Image and Alt Text

Use `PrismicImage` for Prismic image fields. Handle alt text correctly for accessibility.

## PrismicImage Component

Import from `@/components/PrismicImage`. It provides:
- Loading placeholder with fade-in
- Aspect ratio from Prismic dimensions or override
- `fillParent` for filling a sized container
- `prefers-reduced-motion` support

```tsx
import { PrismicImage } from "@/components/PrismicImage";
import { isFilled } from "@prismicio/client";

{isFilled.image(slice.primary.image) && (
  <PrismicImage
    field={slice.primary.image}
    alt={(slice.primary.image.alt || "") as ""}
    imgixParams={{ fit: "crop" }}
    fillParent
    imageStyle={{
      objectFit: "cover",
      objectPosition: "center",
    }}
  />
)}
```

## Alt Text Rules

### Meaningful Images (Content, Hero, Cards)
Pass the Prismic alt text. Use empty string fallback if CMS field is empty:

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD - Pass alt from Prismic field
<PrismicImage
  field={slice.primary.image}
  alt={(slice.primary.image.alt || "") as ""}
  ...
/>
```

**Note**: `PrismicImage` strips duplicate alt when the prop is provided—it uses the prop for the visible `alt` attribute. Pass `field.alt` so editors control accessibility.

### Decorative Images
If an image is purely decorative (doesn't convey information), use empty alt:

```tsx
<PrismicImage
  field={slice.primary.image}
  alt=""
  ...
/>
```

### When to Use Meaningful vs Decorative
- **Meaningful**: Hero images, product images, team photos, screenshots, diagrams, images that add context
- **Decorative**: Background patterns, purely aesthetic imagery, redundant with adjacent text

## PrismicImage Props

| Prop | Type | Description |
|------|------|-------------|
| `field` | ImageField | Prismic image field |
| `alt` | string | Alt text (use `field.alt \|\| ""` for meaningful images) |
| `fillParent` | boolean | Wrapper fills parent (use when parent has fixed size) |
| `aspectRatio` | string | Override e.g. `"16 / 9"` |
| `imgixParams` | object | Imgix params e.g. `{ fit: "crop" }` |
| `imageStyle` | CSSProperties | Styles for the img element |
| `wrapperStyle` | CSSProperties | Styles for the wrapper div |

## When to Use PrismicNextImage Directly

Use raw `PrismicNextImage` only when you need behavior `PrismicImage` doesn't support (e.g. no wrapper, no placeholder). Prefer `PrismicImage` for consistency.

## Do's and Don'ts

### ✅ DO
- Use `PrismicImage` for Prismic image fields
- Pass `field.alt` for meaningful images
- Use `alt=""` for decorative images
- Check `isFilled.image(field)` before rendering
- Use `fillParent` when the parent defines size (e.g. fixed height container)
- Use `imgixParams` for cropping/fitting

### ❌ DON'T
- Don't omit alt for meaningful images
- Don't use redundant alt that repeats adjacent text
- Don't use `alt="image"` or `alt="picture"` as placeholder
